extends layout.pug

block content
    h1.content-title
        i.material-icons feedback
        | Tooltip
    article.box
        .box-body
            h2 Basic
            p You can add tooltips to any element you like. Just add a #[code tooltip] class to it, and by default the #[code title] attribute will be used as the message.
            br
            .text-center
                button.btn-success.tooltip(title='This is a nice tooltip') Hover me
            br
            hr
            h2 Custom message attribute
            p If you need to use the element's #[code title] for another purpose, or if you don't want the default browser's behavior of the title appearing together with the tooltip, you can use the #[code data-tooltip] instead of the #[code title] attribute.
            br
            .text-center
                button.btn-danger.tooltip(title='This title will not appear in the tooltip' data-tooltip='This is the tooltip message') Hover me
            br
            hr
            h2 Placement
            p You can change the default placement of the tooltip (top) with the classes #[code tooltip-left], #[code tooltip-right] and #[code tooltip-bottom].
            br
            .text-center
                button.btn-warning.tooltip(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip') Default
                button.btn-warning.tooltip.tooltip-left(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip') Left
                button.btn-warning.tooltip.tooltip-right(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip') Right
                button.btn-warning.tooltip.tooltip-bottom(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip') Bottom
            br
            hr
            h2 Alignment
            p By default, the tooltip is aligned at the center of the trigger. You can change this by using the classes #[code tooltip-start] and #[code tooltip-end], so the tooltip will be aligned at the start (top or left) or end (bottom or right) limit of the trigger.
            p Try it:
            br
            .text-center
                h3 Top
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-start(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') Start
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') Center
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-end(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') End
            br
            .text-center
                h3 Left
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-left.tooltip-start(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') Start
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-left(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') Center
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-left.tooltip-end(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') End
            br
            .text-center
                h3 Right
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-right.tooltip-start(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') Start
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-right(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') Center
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-right.tooltip-end(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') End
            br
            .text-center
                h3 Bottom
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-bottom.tooltip-start(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') Start
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-bottom(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') Center
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-bottom.tooltip-end(data-tooltip='This is a nice tooltip with a nice content that will break line to show how the alignment works.') End
            br